1
00:00:21,300 --> 00:00:22,767
How can I not be pissed off?

2
00:00:23,933 --> 00:00:25,533
You left me.

3
00:00:27,767 --> 00:00:32,200
You turned your back on me.

4
00:00:32,267 --> 00:00:36,167
I just wanted you
to wait for me.

5
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:43,300
To believe in me...

6
00:00:43,367 --> 00:00:44,767
that someday...

7
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:49,400
I will fulfill my dreams.

8
00:00:50,433 --> 00:00:51,967
But I did.

9
00:00:52,033 --> 00:00:53,567
I believed in you.

10
00:00:56,967 --> 00:00:58,567
I also gambled, right?

11
00:01:02,433 --> 00:01:04,200
I also sacrificed,
remember?

12
00:01:04,267 --> 00:01:05,367
Have you forgotten?

13
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:08,133
You were there.

14
00:01:11,233 --> 00:01:12,933
Have you
forgotten, Celeste?

15
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,967
You have forgotten everything
that I endured?

16
00:01:19,067 --> 00:01:21,867
You have forgotten
everything I did

17
00:01:21,933 --> 00:01:25,700
just to fulfill your dream.

18
00:01:26,800 --> 00:01:31,300
I did everything just
to fulfill your dream.

19
00:01:35,633 --> 00:01:36,600
Everything.

20
00:01:40,033 --> 00:01:41,867
I did everything for you.

21
00:01:41,967 --> 00:01:43,767
What I can't take

22
00:01:43,833 --> 00:01:46,300
is you neglected yourself
for your dream.

23
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:51,233
You might think that
I'm illogical and impulsive.

24
00:01:51,300 --> 00:01:54,633
But if there's one decision
that I'm pretty sure of,

25
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:56,667
its getting married to Celeste.

26
00:01:56,733 --> 00:01:59,733
I'm really sure about
what I feel for her.

27
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:03,067
I'm happy that
you're happy.

28
00:02:03,133 --> 00:02:04,967
So it's all my fault now?

29
00:02:05,033 --> 00:02:08,167
I asked you to choose.
Me or your dream.

30
00:02:08,233 --> 00:02:11,233
Because I have to protect
you from yourself.

31
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:14,667
And you made a choice.

32
00:02:16,233 --> 00:02:18,433
And it wasn't me.

33
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:21,267
I think I don't know you
that well.

34
00:02:21,333 --> 00:02:23,900
I thought I'm included
in your dreams.

35
00:02:23,967 --> 00:02:28,000
I thought I'm included in the
life that you want to fulfill.

36
00:02:28,067 --> 00:02:29,267
But I'm not.

37
00:02:29,333 --> 00:02:31,833
You are willing to give up
everything.

38
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:34,200
You are willing
to forget everything

39
00:02:34,267 --> 00:02:36,533
just to fulfill everything
you want.

40
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:39,033
That's not true.

41
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:40,867
It is.

42
00:02:40,933 --> 00:02:42,200
But, Tiffany, you know what?

43
00:02:43,533 --> 00:02:45,400
I can't take all the credit.

44
00:02:45,467 --> 00:02:48,100
Because the truth is,
I'm guiding you

45
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:50,933
in the direction that you need
to reach.

46
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:55,333
That's why I can't do
all these if not for you.

47
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:58,500
I'm sure you will go back to me.

48
00:02:58,567 --> 00:03:01,300
You're not a good fit
for Celeste.

49
00:03:01,367 --> 00:03:05,733
I'm the only one
who understands you.

50
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:09,233
Why have you so hung up
who between us is at fault?

51
00:03:11,267 --> 00:03:13,300
Because that's what you
make me feel.

52
00:03:13,367 --> 00:03:15,667
You always tell me
it's my fault!

53
00:03:15,733 --> 00:03:16,767
I'm the one who has a problem!

54
00:03:16,833 --> 00:03:20,267
I'm the one who left!
I'm selfish!

55
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:21,700
You're turning
the tables on me!

56
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:24,800
You are like that!

57
00:03:24,867 --> 00:03:27,700
Always, always it's me!

58
00:03:27,767 --> 00:03:29,867
Why are you
doing this to me?

59
00:03:29,933 --> 00:03:33,467
I hate you! I hate you!

60
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:36,567
Why do you have to always be
the nice one?

61
00:04:03,867 --> 00:04:05,133
Go.

62
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:09,033
So tomorrow, lunch?

63
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:12,900
Okay. Anyway, maybe my mother
is already looking for me.

64
00:04:12,967 --> 00:04:15,333
I have to go.

65
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:16,400
You're leaving?

66
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:21,167
Why?

67
00:04:24,567 --> 00:04:26,667
Nothing.

68
00:04:26,733 --> 00:04:30,433
Do you want company?

69
00:04:30,533 --> 00:04:31,733
I can stay here.

70
00:05:11,467 --> 00:05:12,433
Let's go.

71
00:05:19,967 --> 00:05:21,133
What do you mean let's go?

72
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,167
What's that?

73
00:05:22,233 --> 00:05:23,433
Come on.

74
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:24,733
Just trust me.

75
00:05:32,033 --> 00:05:33,033
Oh, Basti.

76
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:35,233
- Okay, Tiffany.
- Okay.

77
00:05:35,333 --> 00:05:37,800
- Let's dance.
- I don't want to.

78
00:05:37,867 --> 00:05:39,867
I don't know how to dance.

79
00:05:39,933 --> 00:05:40,933
No.

80
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,033
Just trust me, okay?

81
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:44,200
It goes like this.

82
00:05:44,267 --> 00:05:51,267
Five, six, seven, eight,
hoo, hoo, to the left...

83
00:05:51,333 --> 00:05:52,533
Oh my God.

84
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:55,200
To the left, go back again...

85
00:05:55,267 --> 00:05:56,867
- join me. Come on!
- I don't want to.

86
00:05:56,933 --> 00:05:57,867
Come on, Tiffany.

87
00:05:57,933 --> 00:06:02,700
Five, six, seven, eight,
backward, forward!

88
00:06:02,767 --> 00:06:04,300
Backward again!

89
00:06:04,367 --> 00:06:07,967
Forward! Five, six, side, side!

90
00:06:08,067 --> 00:06:12,967
Side, now slowly
sway, sway!

91
00:06:13,033 --> 00:06:15,533
Now turn!

92
00:06:51,067 --> 00:06:54,267
Your message feels good.

93
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:25,467
You can't do this to me again.

94
00:08:25,533 --> 00:08:27,667
Hey, wait a second.

95
00:08:27,733 --> 00:08:29,300
Celeste...

96
00:08:31,067 --> 00:08:33,400
don't get mad at me, please.

97
00:08:33,467 --> 00:08:37,833
I didn't mean to make you feel
that I'm blaming you.

98
00:08:37,900 --> 00:08:40,533
It's not important whoever
between us is at fault.

99
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:43,367
Now you're saying that?

100
00:08:43,433 --> 00:08:46,600
You said that it was my fault
and now I should forget it?

101
00:08:48,900 --> 00:08:50,400
It's you who left.

102
00:08:57,100 --> 00:08:59,633
How could you leave me?

103
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:06,700
Do you know what I went through
back then?

104
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:10,800
Do you know that I suffered
from everything

105
00:09:10,867 --> 00:09:14,767
that I've gone through?
You don't know...

106
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:20,367
because you left.

107
00:09:20,433 --> 00:09:23,200
You let the world swallow me.

108
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:55,233
Oh, God.

109
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:56,267
Tiffany...

110
00:09:56,333 --> 00:09:57,500
I'm sorry.

111
00:10:04,933 --> 00:10:06,067
Don't be.

112
00:10:07,233 --> 00:10:10,633
Do you regret now
that you kissed me?

113
00:10:12,233 --> 00:10:13,933
Tiffany, of course not.

114
00:10:16,700 --> 00:10:18,500
I don't want you to think
that I'm taking advantage

115
00:10:18,567 --> 00:10:19,867
of our friendship.

116
00:10:23,433 --> 00:10:26,433
Tiffany, did I offend you?

117
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:27,967
I won't do that again.

118
00:10:28,033 --> 00:10:29,067
It's my fault.

119
00:10:29,133 --> 00:10:30,100
Basti...

120
00:10:32,067 --> 00:10:33,533
it's not all your fault.

121
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:38,900
I also allowed
that to happen.

122
00:10:41,533 --> 00:10:42,800
Do you mean...

123
00:10:44,233 --> 00:10:45,633
you're not angry at me?

124
00:10:54,067 --> 00:10:57,133
Basti, let's not talk
about this again.

125
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:09,233
It's getting kinda late.

126
00:11:09,333 --> 00:11:10,967
I need to go back to my room.

127
00:12:10,067 --> 00:12:12,167
So it's all my fault now?

128
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:17,100
Why are you so hung up
who between us is at fault?

129
00:12:18,767 --> 00:12:20,700
Because that's what
you make me feel.

130
00:12:20,767 --> 00:12:23,500
You always tell me
it's my fault!

131
00:12:23,567 --> 00:12:24,500
I'm the one who
has a problem!

132
00:12:24,567 --> 00:12:28,033
I'm the one who left!
I'm selfish!

133
00:12:28,100 --> 00:12:29,400
You're turning
the tables on me!

134
00:12:29,467 --> 00:12:30,933
You are like that!

135
00:12:32,567 --> 00:12:34,567
Always, always it's me!

136
00:12:34,633 --> 00:12:37,633
Why are you doing this to me?

137
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:41,100
I hate you! I hate you!

138
00:12:41,167 --> 00:12:44,367
Why do you always have
to be the nice one?

139
00:12:58,533 --> 00:13:01,400
I'm the one who was left behind
and I'm wrong.

140
00:13:01,467 --> 00:13:04,133
I'm the bad one. I'm the one
who forgot.

141
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:06,133
It's always me.

142
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,800
And you are the victim.

143
00:13:07,867 --> 00:13:11,533
Not me, Mikoy.

144
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:14,000
It was you who left us.

145
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,867
Celeste, who are
you talking to?

146
00:13:23,967 --> 00:13:25,400
Did something happen?

147
00:13:56,733 --> 00:14:00,533
I know that you and Celeste
are both kind people.

148
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:03,100
I have nothing against
the both of you

149
00:14:03,167 --> 00:14:07,633
but what happened to you
is just a burst of emotions.

150
00:14:07,700 --> 00:14:10,867
Don't worry about that.

151
00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:13,500
That's not a problem
with me, Grandma.

152
00:14:15,267 --> 00:14:17,367
But it seems there is something
with Celeste

153
00:14:17,433 --> 00:14:20,367
that I don't understand.

154
00:14:20,433 --> 00:14:23,433
What is that something?

155
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:29,200
Do you think it has something
to do with Mikoy

156
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:33,133
that's why Celeste
treats me this way?

157
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:35,200
I mean...

158
00:14:35,267 --> 00:14:38,567
do you think
she still likes Mikoy?

159
00:14:38,633 --> 00:14:42,100
That's really what I feel.

160
00:14:42,167 --> 00:14:44,433
You are jealous of Celeste.

161
00:14:45,833 --> 00:14:48,267
Can you blame me for that?

162
00:14:48,333 --> 00:14:50,200
After all, they had
a relationship before.

163
00:14:51,667 --> 00:14:54,633
What's with you?

164
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:58,167
She is getting married.

165
00:14:58,233 --> 00:15:02,233
It means that she has
no feelings for Mikoy anymore.

166
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:06,833
How about Mikoy?

167
00:15:10,767 --> 00:15:12,667
When he and Celeste parted ways

168
00:15:12,733 --> 00:15:14,767
I know that Mikoy got hurt.

169
00:15:16,833 --> 00:15:20,100
You were there for him.

170
00:15:20,167 --> 00:15:24,200
You built his broken dreams.

171
00:15:24,267 --> 00:15:29,433
It was you who helped him
stand up again.

172
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:33,033
Do you think Mikoy
will forget all that?

173
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:35,100
You left...

174
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:38,433
and you came back
where you left him.

175
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:41,567
Do you still doubt
his love for you?

176
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:47,300
You're right,
Grandma Ikay.

177
00:15:47,367 --> 00:15:50,333
I shouldn't doubt Mikoy.

178
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:53,400
And I shouldn't let our
relationship get destroyed

179
00:15:53,467 --> 00:15:56,600
just because of my doubts.

180
00:15:56,667 --> 00:16:00,000
I just hope that Mikoy's love
for me won't change

181
00:16:00,067 --> 00:16:02,600
because he and Celeste
are together again.

182
00:16:33,867 --> 00:16:35,133
Hazel.

183
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:36,900
Mikoy...

184
00:16:36,967 --> 00:16:38,600
good thing you're here.

185
00:16:40,933 --> 00:16:43,033
What are you doing here?

186
00:16:43,133 --> 00:16:44,067
Nothing.

187
00:16:44,133 --> 00:16:45,567
I just miss you.

188
00:16:49,467 --> 00:16:51,000
Where have you been?

189
00:16:51,067 --> 00:16:52,333
Who was with you?

190
00:16:56,133 --> 00:16:58,333
I just went to Ms. Vangie.

191
00:16:58,400 --> 00:17:01,433
I just turned over
some things to her.

192
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:02,533
Let's go upstairs.

193
00:17:05,100 --> 00:17:06,733
- Okay.
- Come on.

194
00:17:59,500 --> 00:18:01,367
Hello.

195
00:18:01,433 --> 00:18:04,933
Good morning.

196
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,567
Hey...

197
00:18:06,633 --> 00:18:08,100
I should go.

198
00:18:08,167 --> 00:18:09,500
No, come on.
Have breakfast first.

199
00:18:09,567 --> 00:18:10,800
I cooked eggs benedict.

200
00:18:10,867 --> 00:18:12,367
Isn't that your favorite?

201
00:18:12,433 --> 00:18:13,600
I got excited because this is
the first time

202
00:18:13,667 --> 00:18:15,133
I cooked it again.

203
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:18,033
I haven't cooked eggs benedict
since we separated.

204
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:21,267
You shouldn't have done that.

205
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:23,333
You shouldn't have gone out
of your way.

206
00:18:23,433 --> 00:18:26,133
And I shouldn't
have slept here.

207
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:27,700
Come on, Tonito.

208
00:18:27,767 --> 00:18:29,700
I know what you're thinking.

209
00:18:29,767 --> 00:18:32,500
I slept in the other room, okay.

210
00:18:32,567 --> 00:18:35,967
You fell asleep that's why
I didn't wake you up

211
00:18:36,033 --> 00:18:37,867
and I know you're tired
from work.

212
00:18:37,933 --> 00:18:38,867
So come on.

213
00:18:38,933 --> 00:18:40,733
Let's just have breakfast, okay?

214
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:41,733
Come on...

215
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:43,400
while your black coffee

216
00:18:43,467 --> 00:18:45,067
with one teaspoon coconut sugar
is still hot.

217
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:49,300
Come on.

218
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:08,267
You've heard what Celeste said?

219
00:19:08,333 --> 00:19:10,333
Yes, last night.

220
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:12,033
I thought she was talking
to Mikoy

221
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:15,267
because she was referring
to him.

222
00:19:15,333 --> 00:19:16,867
Could it be
that the two are fighting?

223
00:19:18,500 --> 00:19:20,067
Don't ask her about that.

224
00:19:20,133 --> 00:19:21,100
She might get embarrassed.

225
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:25,633
I think it has something
to do with Hazel's return.

226
00:19:27,733 --> 00:19:29,533
Could it be...

227
00:19:29,633 --> 00:19:31,833
that they are starting
to like each other again?

228
00:19:31,900 --> 00:19:33,667
Sssh, watch your mouth.

229
00:19:33,733 --> 00:19:35,167
She might hear you.

230
00:19:40,100 --> 00:19:41,933
Celeste, good morning.

231
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:44,067
- Good morning.
- Come on, join us.

232
00:19:44,133 --> 00:19:45,533
Come on.

233
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:46,900
- Plate?
- No.

234
00:19:46,967 --> 00:19:49,400
I think I owe you an apology.

235
00:19:49,467 --> 00:19:50,400
Huh?

236
00:19:50,467 --> 00:19:51,967
Why, Celeste? For what?

237
00:19:57,300 --> 00:20:01,133
About what happened
the other day with Hazel.

238
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:04,700
I'm sorry if our fight
got out of hand.

239
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:06,400
It shouldn't have come to that.

240
00:20:07,867 --> 00:20:11,767
Celeste, don't worry about me
and your Auntie Adora.

241
00:20:11,833 --> 00:20:13,800
We understand.

242
00:20:13,867 --> 00:20:14,900
Your father is right.

243
00:20:14,967 --> 00:20:18,367
I know that you just care
about the farm.

244
00:20:18,433 --> 00:20:21,233
You were just carried away
by what happened.

245
00:20:22,267 --> 00:20:24,767
Maybe I should also
apologize to Hazel.

246
00:20:24,833 --> 00:20:29,300
I don't want her to harbor hate
towards me.

247
00:20:29,367 --> 00:20:31,433
Yes, Celeste.

248
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:34,200
You know, Hazel is a kind
person.

249
00:20:34,267 --> 00:20:39,200
I'm sure she doesn't harbor
any hatred with people.

250
00:20:39,300 --> 00:20:41,067
Just forget about that.

251
00:20:41,133 --> 00:20:42,200
Let's eat.

252
00:20:42,267 --> 00:20:43,533
What do you want?

253
00:20:43,600 --> 00:20:44,667
Eggs?

254
00:20:44,733 --> 00:20:47,467
You will eat breakfast?
How do you want your egg?

255
00:20:47,533 --> 00:20:49,400
Fried, scramble?

256
00:20:49,467 --> 00:20:53,033
Just black coffee.

257
00:20:53,100 --> 00:20:55,333
Black coffee coming up, fresh...

258
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:57,600
- And later...
- Do you want freshly brewed?

259
00:20:57,667 --> 00:20:59,800
Yes but no sugar.

260
00:20:59,867 --> 00:21:02,167
Later, I'll pick some
coconuts for you.

261
00:21:02,233 --> 00:21:05,200
It's summer now,
perfect for the weather.

262
00:21:05,267 --> 00:21:07,733
Coconut juice is the best.

263
00:21:27,433 --> 00:21:30,167
Tiffany, did I offend you?

264
00:21:30,233 --> 00:21:31,667
I won't do that again.

265
00:21:31,733 --> 00:21:32,767
It's my fault.

266
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:33,867
Basti...

267
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:40,000
it's not all your fault.

268
00:21:40,067 --> 00:21:42,500
I also allowed that to happen.

269
00:22:00,733 --> 00:22:02,767
Wrong, wrong.

270
00:22:02,833 --> 00:22:04,367
It's wrong.

271
00:22:28,333 --> 00:22:30,167
Hello, Mikoy.

272
00:22:30,233 --> 00:22:32,033
Hey...

273
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:34,300
why are you here?
Do you need anything?

274
00:22:34,367 --> 00:22:35,433
Not you.

275
00:22:35,500 --> 00:22:37,633
I want to talk to Hazel.

276
00:22:37,700 --> 00:22:40,200
I want to apologize to her.

277
00:22:40,267 --> 00:22:42,033
Can you accompany me to her?

278
00:22:45,667 --> 00:22:46,967
Perfect. She's here.

279
00:22:54,633 --> 00:22:55,733
Come on.

280
00:23:07,100 --> 00:23:10,433
Don't tell me that
you have doubts about Mikoy?

281
00:23:10,500 --> 00:23:13,767
I trust Mikoy.

282
00:23:13,833 --> 00:23:16,467
I know that he's faithful to me.

283
00:23:16,533 --> 00:23:17,967
You know...

284
00:23:18,033 --> 00:23:21,633
trust in a relationship
is very important.

285
00:23:21,700 --> 00:23:23,933
If you start to doubt...

286
00:23:24,033 --> 00:23:27,467
that's the rust
that will destroy you.

287
00:23:27,533 --> 00:23:29,833
I won't let that happen to us.

288
00:23:29,900 --> 00:23:32,600
I trust Mikoy...

289
00:23:32,667 --> 00:23:36,333
but it's Celeste
that I have doubts about.

290
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:41,233
I don't know her but I can smell
her character.

291
00:23:42,767 --> 00:23:44,200
It's a bit bad.

292
00:23:54,233 --> 00:23:55,233
Hazel...

293
00:23:56,900 --> 00:23:58,400
someone wants
to talk to you.

294
00:24:34,300 --> 00:24:35,433
How are you and Mikoy?

295
00:24:35,500 --> 00:24:37,900
I have a feeling that
you are really affected

296
00:24:37,967 --> 00:24:39,167
by Hazel's arrival.

297
00:24:40,567 --> 00:24:42,600
Silence means yes.

298
00:24:42,667 --> 00:24:44,400
Are you keeping
a secret from me?

299
00:24:44,467 --> 00:24:46,367
Why do you have to hide
from me

300
00:24:46,433 --> 00:24:48,300
that Celeste was with you
last night?

301
00:24:48,367 --> 00:24:49,600
You have to move fast

302
00:24:49,667 --> 00:24:51,333
because in a few months from now

303
00:24:51,400 --> 00:24:53,400
Tonito will be married
to Celeste.

304
00:24:53,467 --> 00:24:54,433
You'll never know.

305
00:24:57,667 --> 00:24:58,600
Wow, that brown envelope
is lucky.

306
00:24:58,667 --> 00:25:01,267
Oh my God.

307
00:25:01,333 --> 00:25:02,767
It has received a lot
of kisses from you.

308
00:25:02,867 --> 00:25:03,967
What's wrong with you?

309
00:25:04,033 --> 00:25:06,333
It seems like someone
is preventing our marriage.

310
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:08,700
Am I stuck here
in Sorsogon forever?

311
00:25:08,767 --> 00:25:11,600
Aurelia is your ex-wife, Tonito.

312
00:25:11,667 --> 00:25:14,067
Spending the night with her
will only create doubts.

313
00:25:14,133 --> 00:25:16,033
Sebastian visits us often.

314
00:25:16,100 --> 00:25:17,400
He is with his girlfriend.

315
00:25:17,467 --> 00:25:18,633
- Girlfriend?
- Girlfriend?

316
00:25:18,700 --> 00:25:20,367
Celeste...

317
00:25:20,433 --> 00:25:21,667
Celeste, I'm really sorry.

318
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:25,300
Is Mikoy with you?

319
00:25:25,367 --> 00:25:27,767
He went to Celeste
in her house.
